# Nuxt 3 + Vue 3 ŌĆö Project Rules

## Auto-imports

Nuxt 3 auto-imports the following ŌĆö never import them manually:
- Vue primitives: `ref`, `reactive`, `computed`, `watch`, `watchEffect`,
  `onMounted`, `onUnmounted`, and all other Composition API utilities
- Nuxt composables: `useRouter`, `useRoute`, `useState`, `useFetch`,
  `useAsyncData`, `useHead`, `useSeoMeta`, `useRuntimeConfig`,
  `navigateTo`, `definePageMeta`
- Components in `components/` and composables in `composables/` directories

The exception is `motion` from `motion-v` ŌĆö this is not auto-imported and
must always be imported manually.

## Code style

- Functional and declarative patterns throughout ŌĆö avoid classes
- DRY principle: prefer iteration and modularisation over duplication
- Composition API with `<script setup>` only ŌĆö never Options API
- Descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs: `isLoading`, `hasError`,
  `isVisible`, `hasContent`

## Naming conventions

- Components: PascalCase filenames (`components/WorkCard.vue`)
- Composables: camelCase with `use` prefix (`composables/useWorkItems.ts`)
- Pages: lowercase with dashes (`pages/about.vue`, `pages/work/[slug].vue`)
- Named exports for composables and utilities ŌĆö avoid default exports
  except for Vue components and Nuxt config

## Data fetching

Use `useFetch` for straightforward data fetching:
```ts
const { data, status } = await useFetch('/api/work')
```

Use `useAsyncData` for complex cases ŌĆö combining multiple calls, custom
caching, or specific error handling:
```ts
const { data } = await useAsyncData('work-items', () => {
  return Promise.all([fetchWork(), fetchPlay()])
})
```

Set `server: false` to fetch only on the client side (bypasses SSR):
```ts
const { data } = await useFetch('/api/items', { server: false })
```

Set `lazy: true` to defer non-critical data fetching until after the
initial render:
```ts
const { data } = await useFetch('/api/items', { lazy: true })
```

## SEO and metadata

Every page must define metadata. Use `useSeoMeta` as the default:
```ts
useSeoMeta({
  title: 'Page Title ŌĆö designwithjack',
  description: 'Page description.'
})
```

Use `useHead` for anything beyond title and description (canonical URLs,
Open Graph, structured data):
```ts
useHead({
  link: [{ rel: 'canonical', href: 'https://designwithjack.com/work' }]
})
```

Never hardcode `<title>` or `<meta>` tags in templates.

## Images

Use `<NuxtImage>` or `<NuxtPicture>` for all images. Requires
`@nuxt/image` to be installed and added to modules. Benefits: automatic
WebP conversion, lazy loading, responsive sizing. Never use a plain `<img>`
tag for content images.

## Routing

- File-based routing in `pages/` ŌĆö do not manually configure routes
- Dynamic segments use bracket syntax: `pages/work/[slug].vue`
- Use `definePageMeta` for page-level configuration:
  ```ts
  definePageMeta({
    layout: 'default'
  })
  ```
- Use `navigateTo()` for programmatic navigation inside composables
  and middleware ŌĆö use `<NuxtLink>` in templates

## State management

- Local component state: `ref` and `reactive`
- SSR-safe shared state that survives hydration: `useState`
- Do not reach for Pinia unless state complexity clearly justifies it ŌĆö
  it is not installed in this project

## Performance

- Use `<Suspense>` for async components where appropriate
- Lazy load heavy components with `defineAsyncComponent`
- Prefer `<NuxtImage>` over `<img>` for automatic optimisation
- Avoid animating layout properties (height, width, padding, margin) ŌĆö
  use transform-based alternatives
